WEBVTT

00:00:30.322 --> 00:00:33.951
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

00:00:44.044 --> 00:00:46.879
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION SOME SCENES WERE GENERATED USING AI

00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:48.966
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS WERE FILMED SAFELY

00:00:55.472 --> 00:00:57.056
CONDOLENCES

00:00:57.057 --> 00:00:59.517
THE LATE OH MIJA

00:01:02.813 --> 00:01:06.275
Why were you in such a rush to leave us

00:01:07.192 --> 00:01:10.821
And walk down such a scary road all alone?

00:01:17.661 --> 00:01:19.036
By the way,

00:01:19.037 --> 00:01:21.581
What's taking the picture frame so long to get here?

00:01:21.582 --> 00:01:23.250
This doesn't look good at all.

00:01:23.917 --> 00:01:26.128
They said it's coming with the evening ferry.

00:01:27.004 --> 00:01:30.006
But where's Ms. Hari?

00:01:30.007 --> 00:01:33.009
I brought some porridge to help her regain some strength.

00:01:33.010 --> 00:01:34.135
Right.

00:01:34.136 --> 00:01:36.929
She was definitely here a minute ago.

00:01:36.930 --> 00:01:39.683
Goodness, where has she gone? Huh?

00:02:16.887 --> 00:02:18.179
I'll go look for her.

00:02:18.180 --> 00:02:19.765
- Okay. - I'll go with you.

00:02:22.267 --> 00:02:23.310
Ms. Yuk.

00:02:35.405 --> 00:02:37.198
Hari, what are you doing?

00:02:38.617 --> 00:02:39.618
My grandma

00:02:41.244 --> 00:02:43.205
Likes my pasta more than anything else.

00:02:46.917 --> 00:02:48.669
I couldn't do anything for her.

00:02:57.344 --> 00:02:59.053
So this is the least I could do.

00:03:43.682 --> 00:03:45.434
:cue

00:04:52.626 --> 00:04:54.503
What are you doing here alone?

00:04:58.340 --> 00:04:59.758
I thought you might be cold.

00:05:03.637 --> 00:05:04.638
Have you

00:05:06.640 --> 00:05:07.766
Had anything to eat?

00:05:09.392 --> 00:05:12.020
It's not like Pyeondongdo will ever let me go hungry.

00:05:13.855 --> 00:05:15.565
Everyone kept feeding me nonstop.

00:05:17.359 --> 00:05:20.486
They brought me breakfast, lunch, dinner, and even dessert,

00:05:20.487 --> 00:05:23.448
Saying I'll need a full belly to have the energy to grieve.

00:05:30.288 --> 00:05:31.289
I'm

00:05:37.295 --> 00:05:39.381
I'm going to stay strong and stop crying

00:05:41.716 --> 00:05:43.635
To give my grandma a proper send-off.

00:05:48.098 --> 00:05:51.268
Whenever I cried, my grandma used to go three days without sleep

00:05:52.227 --> 00:05:53.728
Because it tore her up inside.

00:06:02.153 --> 00:06:04.072
Can I also count on your help, Dr. Do?

00:06:13.707 --> 00:06:15.584
Please just pretend you don't see me.

00:06:22.257 --> 00:06:25.093
I don't hate you or anything

00:06:29.097 --> 00:06:32.100
But every time I see you, I feel like breaking down in tears.

00:06:39.399 --> 00:06:40.859
You understand, right?

00:07:08.261 --> 00:07:15.226
EPISODE 8 I CAN'T DO IT. I CAN'T IGNORE YOU.

00:07:22.942 --> 00:07:25.654
:cue

00:08:04.401 --> 00:08:06.361
FOR EXCELLENCE

00:08:51.698 --> 00:08:53.699
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

00:08:53.700 --> 00:08:54.992
Hello, everyone.

00:08:54.993 --> 00:08:56.076
- Ms. Yuk. - Ms. Yuk.

00:08:56.077 --> 00:08:58.495
Why'd you come to work already?

00:08:58.496 --> 00:09:00.915
Of course I should. We're not done with the surveys.

00:09:09.758 --> 00:09:12.927
Thanks to all of you, I was able to give my grandma a proper farewell.

00:09:14.429 --> 00:09:16.555
You made the right call coming to work.

00:09:16.556 --> 00:09:19.558
Someone high-octane like you only struggles when stuck at home.

00:09:21.311 --> 00:09:25.106
Right.

00:09:30.236 --> 00:09:31.321
Help us!

00:09:32.113 --> 00:09:36.116
Please help us or he's really going to die!

00:09:41.581 --> 00:09:45.376
Over here! He's bleeding all over right now!

00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:50.006
- Sangjin! - Over here! Hurry!

00:09:50.673 --> 00:09:53.133
Get out of the way!

00:09:53.134 --> 00:09:54.635
I'll hold it down.

00:09:58.556 --> 00:10:00.808
- Get an IV line going. Start Hartmann's. - Okay.

00:10:00.809 --> 00:10:02.518
INTRAVENOUS LINE IV FLUID

00:10:02.519 --> 00:10:03.978
Sir, can you hear me?

00:10:04.562 --> 00:10:06.230
- I can. - Okay.

00:10:06.231 --> 00:10:07.565
He's got a weak pulse.

00:10:11.194 --> 00:10:12.861
I think a major vessel's compromised.

00:10:12.862 --> 00:10:16.282
Seems like the jugular is severed, with possible carotid damage.

00:10:16.866 --> 00:10:18.075
What are you going to do?

00:10:18.076 --> 00:10:20.536
I don't think transporting him is an option right now.

00:10:20.537 --> 00:10:22.496
Let's pack the wound. I'll clamp the vessel.

00:10:22.497 --> 00:10:23.664
Here?

00:10:23.665 --> 00:10:25.207
Yes. Keep holding pressure.

00:10:25.208 --> 00:10:28.585
APPLYING DIRECT PRESSURE TO THE WOUND TO STOP BLEEDING

00:10:28.586 --> 00:10:30.547
- Please hold this up for me. - Okay.

00:11:10.503 --> 00:11:12.463
Okay, I got it.

00:11:13.673 --> 00:11:16.258
-  Okay. -  Pack it with the gauze.

00:11:19.429 --> 00:11:20.513
Hello?

00:11:23.725 --> 00:11:25.976
- What? - What is it?

00:11:27.103 --> 00:11:30.063
They're saying the helicopter can't land because of the construction

00:11:30.064 --> 00:11:31.899
And that a medical boat will be faster.

00:11:31.900 --> 00:11:33.025
What do you mean?

00:11:33.026 --> 00:11:34.735
We have no time!

00:11:34.736 --> 00:11:36.738
He's lost so much blood already!

00:11:38.239 --> 00:11:40.073
Let's move him first. Please help me.

00:11:40.074 --> 00:11:43.745
Come over here and grab him. We'll be moving the patient.

00:11:46.915 --> 00:11:49.666
Looks like a partial tear to the right carotid.

00:11:49.667 --> 00:11:52.544
The SCM's blown, and there's a partial EJV transection.

00:11:52.545 --> 00:11:55.130
He's mentally clear and vitals are stable. He's all yours.

00:11:55.131 --> 00:11:58.008
Thank you for your hard work. We'll take it from here. :cue

00:11:58.009 --> 00:11:59.218
Best of luck.

00:12:02.597 --> 00:12:05.892
Doctor, Sangjin's going to be okay, right?

00:12:06.434 --> 00:12:09.354
Yes, he should be fine as long as the surgery goes well.

00:12:10.313 --> 00:12:12.065
What the hell is going on?

00:12:14.692 --> 00:12:16.361
Goddamn it!

00:12:18.863 --> 00:12:21.074
Another accident? What is it this time?

00:12:21.783 --> 00:12:24.202
Are you freaking kidding me right now?

00:12:24.994 --> 00:12:29.289
How do you keep screwing up and causing so many damn accidents?

00:12:29.290 --> 00:12:32.542
I told you we couldn't do it! I told you we couldn't meet that deadline!

00:12:32.543 --> 00:12:36.380
People are only getting injured because you keep rushing us!

00:12:36.381 --> 00:12:39.591
That's why I told you to stick to the safety protocols!

00:12:39.592 --> 00:12:42.052
Why are you blaming me after mucking up your job?

00:12:42.053 --> 00:12:44.805
We set the deadline to match the day of the governor's visit,

00:12:44.806 --> 00:12:46.390
So stop talking out of your ass.

00:12:46.391 --> 00:12:48.892
-  You - Hey, what are you doing?

00:12:48.893 --> 00:12:51.687
A man's about to die, and all you care about

00:12:51.688 --> 00:12:53.522
Is the day of the governor's visit?

00:12:53.523 --> 00:12:56.858
Geez, here we go again with this shit.

00:12:56.859 --> 00:12:58.360
Let go. Have you lost it?

00:12:58.361 --> 00:13:00.529
A man almost died!

00:13:00.530 --> 00:13:02.864
I said, let go!

00:13:02.865 --> 00:13:04.950
Holy crap! It's one thing after another!

00:13:06.035 --> 00:13:08.829
- What does that have to do with me? - What's the matter with you?

00:13:08.830 --> 00:13:10.832
- You stay out of this. -  Are you okay, sir?

00:13:12.041 --> 00:13:14.751
You do realize this counts as an industrial accident, right?

00:13:14.752 --> 00:13:17.045
Project supervisors are liable for them.

00:13:17.046 --> 00:13:18.672
If they hold you responsible for--

00:13:18.673 --> 00:13:21.591
Not this law crap again!

00:13:21.592 --> 00:13:23.427
I can't take this anymore.

00:13:23.428 --> 00:13:25.595
So stay out of this, miss.

00:13:25.596 --> 00:13:27.014
I said, stay out of it!

00:13:27.015 --> 00:13:28.141
Huh?

00:13:28.933 --> 00:13:30.892
Let go of me.

00:13:30.893 --> 00:13:33.020
Oh, for the love of

00:13:34.981 --> 00:13:36.316
D-Dr. Hyeon

00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:41.820
I thought I warned you not to cross me a third time!

00:13:41.821 --> 00:13:44.741
I don't think you're the one in charge of this construction project.

00:13:45.825 --> 00:13:48.536
Since this is a Yeopoong-gun project, isn't it the governor?

00:13:51.247 --> 00:13:53.623
File a claim for workers' compensation

00:13:53.624 --> 00:13:55.918
With the governor of Yeopoong-gun right now.

00:13:56.502 --> 00:13:57.503
What?

00:13:58.337 --> 00:13:59.921
There's no need for that.

00:13:59.922 --> 00:14:01.506
Why bring the governor into this?

00:14:01.507 --> 00:14:03.216
Okay, I get it.

00:14:03.217 --> 00:14:04.218
I said, I get it.

00:14:20.735 --> 00:14:24.030
That damn construction project's really going to get someone killed!

00:14:24.739 --> 00:14:25.740
Hmm?

00:14:26.407 --> 00:14:28.493
How badly are they running it

00:14:29.202 --> 00:14:31.412
To cause this many injuries?

00:14:33.539 --> 00:14:34.749
Goodness

00:14:36.167 --> 00:14:37.335
Dr. Hyeon.

00:14:39.045 --> 00:14:40.630
Let's put some ointment on that.

00:14:59.690 --> 00:15:00.775
By the way

00:15:01.609 --> 00:15:04.569
It's a bit odd that you told me to follow you,

00:15:04.570 --> 00:15:06.072
Only to have me apply it myself.

00:15:06.697 --> 00:15:09.449
Your hand's fine, so it's better to do it yourself.

00:15:11.244 --> 00:15:13.955
Why'd you tell me to come if you weren't going to do it for me?

00:15:17.458 --> 00:15:20.211
Because I was grateful for your help.

00:15:24.006 --> 00:15:26.843
To be honest, I was really scared earlier.

00:15:33.391 --> 00:15:34.392
Really?

00:15:35.685 --> 00:15:37.519
I had no idea.

00:15:37.520 --> 00:15:41.274
If anything, I thought he was the one who was really scared.

00:15:42.191 --> 00:15:43.818
Come on, no way.

00:15:47.363 --> 00:15:50.490
No, seriously. I bet you could beat him in a fight.

00:15:53.995 --> 00:15:56.079
- You used to fight a lot in school, right? - Hey.

00:15:56.080 --> 00:15:58.790
- He's a doctor. -  You've got this aura about you

00:15:58.791 --> 00:16:01.668
I'm sure he's better at treating himself.

00:16:14.015 --> 00:16:15.390
Hey, that hurts.

00:16:15.391 --> 00:16:18.060
Why do they keep laughing so much? :cue

00:16:26.777 --> 00:16:28.820
I feel bad for Dr. Jiui.

00:16:28.821 --> 00:16:31.365
Wow. There are worse reasons to pity someone.

00:16:32.742 --> 00:16:35.660
Dr. Jiui still likes Ms. Hari.

00:16:35.661 --> 00:16:38.246
If he likes her so much, why did he do that?

00:16:38.247 --> 00:16:43.043
I heard he also helped Ms. Hari's grandma with the advance directive.

00:16:43.044 --> 00:16:45.128
That's because he's a doctor.

00:16:45.129 --> 00:16:48.089
He's a boyfriend first and a doctor second.

00:16:48.090 --> 00:16:50.592
Do you think she needed a doctor by her side

00:16:50.593 --> 00:16:52.719
When her only family member was about to pass away?

00:16:52.720 --> 00:16:55.347
She needed someone who would take her side no matter what,

00:16:55.348 --> 00:16:56.973
And lend her an ear.

00:16:56.974 --> 00:16:58.516
But still

00:16:58.517 --> 00:17:04.356
I'm saying, you can't always figure out matters of the heart with logic.

00:17:04.357 --> 00:17:06.316
Even if something makes sense in your head,

00:17:06.317 --> 00:17:08.277
It might not in your heart.

00:17:11.697 --> 00:17:13.115
I won't do that to you.

00:17:14.492 --> 00:17:17.662
I'll take your side, no matter what happens.

00:17:18.996 --> 00:17:21.665
Hmm We'll see about that.

00:17:21.666 --> 00:17:23.125
I mean it, though.

00:17:27.296 --> 00:17:28.381
Let's go.

00:17:28.923 --> 00:17:29.924
Hmm?

00:17:30.925 --> 00:17:32.760
I haven't seen those flowers before.

00:17:34.637 --> 00:17:38.765
I was expecting a guest, so I figured they would look nice.

00:17:38.766 --> 00:17:41.017
Hmm

00:17:41.018 --> 00:17:42.103
A guest?

00:17:42.687 --> 00:17:43.729
Hmm?

00:17:49.402 --> 00:17:51.653
They're so pretty! Really!

00:17:51.654 --> 00:17:55.031
Your guest loves them so much.

00:17:55.032 --> 00:17:56.408
Hmm

00:17:56.409 --> 00:17:57.785
Since it's raining and all

00:18:01.998 --> 00:18:05.208
Your guest would like to stay over for some ramyeon.

00:18:11.591 --> 00:18:16.470
The thing is, I'm actually all out of ramyeon.

00:18:18.347 --> 00:18:20.599
Would you mind grabbing some? Two should do.

00:18:20.600 --> 00:18:21.642
Two?

00:18:25.229 --> 00:18:26.230
Really?

00:18:27.565 --> 00:18:30.693
I'm really going to bring some back, okay? Two.

00:18:35.156 --> 00:18:37.115
- Dr. Jucheon! - Yes?

00:18:37.116 --> 00:18:40.286
We shouldn't have ramyeon so late at night. Go home and sleep!

00:18:48.294 --> 00:18:49.712
Oh, man!

00:18:53.466 --> 00:18:55.635
Is she playing games with me?

00:18:56.302 --> 00:18:59.722
She's the one who told me to get two. That was such a rare opportunity too.

00:19:01.432 --> 00:19:05.185
Goodness me, it sure is raining hard.

00:19:05.186 --> 00:19:07.271
What's with all this rain?

00:19:08.939 --> 00:19:10.440
Granny, it's me.

00:19:10.441 --> 00:19:11.566
Oh, you're here?

00:19:11.567 --> 00:19:12.859
Have you eaten yet?

00:19:12.860 --> 00:19:15.528
- Of course I have. It's so late. - Yeah?

00:19:15.529 --> 00:19:19.074
Gosh, this rain. It doesn't bode well.

00:19:19.075 --> 00:19:20.367
You're right.

00:19:20.368 --> 00:19:23.746
On days like this, be sure to shut your windows tight.

00:19:24.246 --> 00:19:26.791
Don't worry. My grandma's going to

00:19:30.127 --> 00:19:32.922
Goodness, I shouldn't have said that.

00:19:34.048 --> 00:19:35.424
What?

00:19:36.384 --> 00:19:38.385
- The windows! - Hmm?

00:19:38.386 --> 00:19:39.387
- Oh, no! - Oh, my.

00:19:40.179 --> 00:19:42.180
Granny, I'm going!

00:19:42.181 --> 00:19:43.264
Okay.

00:19:43.265 --> 00:19:44.849
LUCKY SUPERMARKET

00:19:44.850 --> 00:19:46.268
Hurry

00:19:58.406 --> 00:19:59.907
Oh, no!

00:20:10.418 --> 00:20:11.419
No!

00:20:20.302 --> 00:20:21.345
Gosh!

00:20:26.142 --> 00:20:27.226
Oh

00:20:33.858 --> 00:20:35.651
What's happening?

00:20:37.528 --> 00:20:38.529
:cue

00:20:57.298 --> 00:20:59.467
Oh, my.

00:21:00.134 --> 00:21:04.345
It poured like crazy yesterday, but it's sunny as ever outside today.

00:21:04.346 --> 00:21:06.973
Winter weather is always fickle like that.

00:21:06.974 --> 00:21:08.017
Right.

00:21:12.104 --> 00:21:13.354
- Huh? - Huh?

00:21:13.355 --> 00:21:15.024
What the heck is that?

00:21:15.608 --> 00:21:16.650
Huh?

00:21:21.614 --> 00:21:23.031
Huh?

00:21:23.032 --> 00:21:24.491
What is all this?

00:21:24.492 --> 00:21:29.704
Hello. I'm having some issues back at home, so

00:21:29.705 --> 00:21:31.748
What kind of issues made you pack your things?

00:21:31.749 --> 00:21:34.292
There's a leak in my roof,

00:21:34.293 --> 00:21:37.837
So Mr. Park took a look at it for me and said that fixing it will take days.

00:21:37.838 --> 00:21:40.382
A leak? That's bad.

00:21:41.050 --> 00:21:43.176
So I wanted to ask

00:21:43.177 --> 00:21:47.097
Could I stay here for a while until they're done fixing my house?

00:21:48.182 --> 00:21:50.350
- You want to sleep at the center? - Yes.

00:21:50.351 --> 00:21:52.852
We have quite a few chairs and beds here, so

00:21:52.853 --> 00:21:55.188
You can't do that.

00:21:55.189 --> 00:21:57.107
That would be so uncomfortable.

00:21:58.400 --> 00:22:01.194
Just come to my house instead.

00:22:01.195 --> 00:22:02.403
What?

00:22:02.404 --> 00:22:04.322
No, that's fine.

00:22:04.323 --> 00:22:07.283
How could I stay at your house when your husband's there?

00:22:07.284 --> 00:22:09.828
If you're uncomfortable, he can just stay somewhere else.

00:22:11.497 --> 00:22:14.791
Then you should stay at Ms. Jeongseon's house.

00:22:14.792 --> 00:22:16.876
My house?

00:22:16.877 --> 00:22:18.628
You live alone anyway,

00:22:18.629 --> 00:22:22.006
So just let her crash there for a few days like you're sisters.

00:22:22.007 --> 00:22:26.094
I am so sorry, but I'm actually expecting a guest.

00:22:26.095 --> 00:22:28.180
Hey, it's fine.

00:22:28.681 --> 00:22:31.725
-  Come stay at our quarters. - Sorry?

00:22:33.310 --> 00:22:35.270
The quarters were made for medical personnel,

00:22:35.271 --> 00:22:38.232
So it's okay for you to use them, and we've got plenty of rooms.

00:22:38.983 --> 00:22:42.026
Sure, we have a lot of rooms, but they're all occupied.

00:22:42.027 --> 00:22:45.780
- It's - Yes! That sounds like the best option.

00:22:45.781 --> 00:22:50.159
I've been concerned about you living alone,

00:22:50.160 --> 00:22:54.706
But it'll be great having a full house here at the quarters, right?

00:22:54.707 --> 00:22:58.084
You'll also feel less lonely that way.

00:23:00.588 --> 00:23:02.046
Is this everything?

00:23:02.047 --> 00:23:04.091
But, I

00:23:10.139 --> 00:23:13.058
Just stay here. That'll put everyone at ease.

00:23:13.684 --> 00:23:15.560
If you insist on sleeping over there,

00:23:15.561 --> 00:23:19.188
Everyone on Pyeondongdo will be worried sick about you.

00:23:19.189 --> 00:23:21.650
So that settles everything, right?

00:23:22.526 --> 00:23:25.653
Gosh, that puts my mind at ease.

00:23:25.654 --> 00:23:27.114
-  Thank you. - Of course.

00:23:28.115 --> 00:23:29.491
- Let's go, Dr. Do. - Okay.

00:23:48.260 --> 00:23:50.179
What time should your guest come over?

00:23:50.846 --> 00:23:52.513
What are you talking about?

00:23:52.514 --> 00:23:56.142
The guest you were talking about was me, wasn't it?

00:23:56.143 --> 00:23:58.686
Geez, what nonsense is this?

00:23:58.687 --> 00:24:00.980
Did you really think I'd be so desperate for a man

00:24:00.981 --> 00:24:03.399
That I'd turn Ms. Hari away for you?

00:24:03.400 --> 00:24:04.817
What the

00:24:04.818 --> 00:24:07.613
Then someone's actually coming over?

00:24:08.238 --> 00:24:09.239
Who is it?

00:24:11.200 --> 00:24:14.160
You wouldn't know even if I told you.

00:24:14.161 --> 00:24:16.663
I wouldn't know, but I have a right to ask.

00:24:16.664 --> 00:24:17.998
I'm your boyfriend.

00:24:20.709 --> 00:24:22.752
It's a friend.

00:24:22.753 --> 00:24:25.588
My friend is visiting Pyeondongdo for the first time in a while,

00:24:25.589 --> 00:24:27.590
So I agreed to let them stay for a few days.

00:24:27.591 --> 00:24:28.800
Hmm

00:24:28.801 --> 00:24:32.387
You must be close if you're letting them stay over.

00:24:32.388 --> 00:24:34.056
Why don't you introduce me?

00:24:34.807 --> 00:24:35.891
Introduce you?

00:24:36.642 --> 00:24:40.354
Yes. A friend of yours is a friend of mine, after all.

00:24:43.649 --> 00:24:44.857
Forget it, okay?

00:24:44.858 --> 00:24:47.860
We're not even that close, and they won't be staying long.

00:24:47.861 --> 00:24:51.699
Gosh, we always get a lot of patients around this time, so get to work.

00:24:53.742 --> 00:24:54.743
Hmm.

00:24:55.452 --> 00:24:59.039
Why won't she introduce me to her friend? What's going on?

00:25:00.207 --> 00:25:01.834
Is she shy or what? :cue

00:25:07.089 --> 00:25:08.172
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

00:25:08.173 --> 00:25:10.467
Hello. Welcome to the staff quarters.

00:25:11.051 --> 00:25:13.177
I hope I don't make things too awkward for you.

00:25:13.178 --> 00:25:17.182
Come on, it won't be awkward at all. The more, the merrier.

00:25:18.267 --> 00:25:20.643
You should get some rest now. Your room is this--

00:25:20.644 --> 00:25:22.020
Stay in this one.

00:25:24.898 --> 00:25:28.151
This is the biggest room and it's also got a view of the ocean.

00:25:28.152 --> 00:25:31.029
- I'm on call anyway, so -  Hmm.

00:25:31.030 --> 00:25:32.989
Yeah, you should stay in this one.

00:25:32.990 --> 00:25:36.367
Dr. Jiui made a huge fuss cleaning that room.

00:25:36.368 --> 00:25:39.454
- Why would you bring that up? - You did, didn't you?

00:25:39.455 --> 00:25:42.665
You even wiped down the shelves with disinfecting wipes like in an OR.

00:25:42.666 --> 00:25:44.793
Go ahead and get some rest. You must be tired.

00:25:46.295 --> 00:25:48.171
You should head inside.

00:25:48.172 --> 00:25:50.549
Okay. Then

00:26:05.689 --> 00:26:06.690
Then

00:26:07.941 --> 00:26:10.234
Sleep tight, you two.

00:26:10.235 --> 00:26:12.029
Though I'm not sure if you'll be able to.

00:26:23.082 --> 00:26:25.500
If you're uncomfortable sleeping in the living room

00:26:25.501 --> 00:26:26.793
No, not at all.

00:26:26.794 --> 00:26:28.837
Okay then.

00:26:34.134 --> 00:26:35.969
That jerk.

00:27:45.622 --> 00:27:47.373
PUBLIC HEALTH CENTER

00:27:47.374 --> 00:27:49.042
CLOSED

00:28:24.244 --> 00:28:25.454
:cue

00:28:31.752 --> 00:28:32.753
Dr. Do.

00:28:33.921 --> 00:28:35.046
Dr. Do!

00:28:39.051 --> 00:28:40.468
Look at you.

00:28:40.469 --> 00:28:43.388
Snoring away without a care in the world while your ex is around.

00:28:44.181 --> 00:28:45.848
What is it?

00:28:45.849 --> 00:28:48.310
- Get up. We're having breakfast. - What?

00:28:48.977 --> 00:28:51.103
Breakfast? All of a sudden?

00:28:51.104 --> 00:28:53.397
Ms. Hari wanted to pay us back for letting her stay.

00:29:01.406 --> 00:29:03.867
Do you really feel nothing when you see that?

00:29:04.993 --> 00:29:07.787
Don't you see that man who's standing there

00:29:07.788 --> 00:29:09.956
With his hair done at the crack of dawn?

00:29:09.957 --> 00:29:14.669
The early bird gets extra time to sing a love serenade.

00:29:14.670 --> 00:29:15.921
Get up quickly.

00:29:17.464 --> 00:29:19.883
- Thank you so much. - Of course. Enjoy.

00:29:22.302 --> 00:29:25.304
Oh! Let me grab some ketchup for you guys.

00:29:30.435 --> 00:29:33.355
If you're not going to do anything, at least try to enjoy the food.

00:29:38.860 --> 00:29:39.861
There

00:29:46.034 --> 00:29:47.201
This is really delicious.

00:29:47.202 --> 00:29:49.663
It really is.

00:29:52.290 --> 00:29:53.333
Gosh

00:29:58.338 --> 00:30:02.175
Why are you complaining to me that you ran out of cigarettes?

00:30:04.219 --> 00:30:05.886
I don't know.

00:30:05.887 --> 00:30:08.514
And you'd better not smoke in the room.

00:30:08.515 --> 00:30:10.683
- Ms. Eom. - Yes?

00:30:10.684 --> 00:30:12.477
Did your friend make it here okay?

00:30:13.353 --> 00:30:15.354
Yes.

00:30:15.355 --> 00:30:18.024
You weren't picking up, so I just called you once,

00:30:18.025 --> 00:30:19.317
Then went straight to bed.

00:30:19.818 --> 00:30:23.237
You called? Things were really hectic, so

00:30:23.238 --> 00:30:26.157
Mmm How long have you been friends?

00:30:26.158 --> 00:30:29.953
Have you known them since middle school? High school?

00:30:31.371 --> 00:30:35.207
We're just friends.

00:30:35.208 --> 00:30:36.625
Mmm

00:30:36.626 --> 00:30:38.586
So you've been friends for a while, huh?

00:30:38.587 --> 00:30:42.256
I'm dying to get to know your friend.

00:30:42.257 --> 00:30:45.301
Can't we meet up? I'll treat you guys--

00:30:45.302 --> 00:30:47.262
I told you, no.

00:30:51.475 --> 00:30:52.517
Ms. Eom.

00:30:53.894 --> 00:30:58.273
Why do you keep trying to butt into someone else's private life?

00:31:00.192 --> 00:31:01.442
S

00:31:01.443 --> 00:31:03.570
S-Someone else's?

00:31:07.657 --> 00:31:08.658
Oh

00:31:09.242 --> 00:31:10.744
What I meant is

00:31:11.912 --> 00:31:15.332
I was just curious as to what kind of childhood you had,

00:31:16.374 --> 00:31:18.126
Since you're someone I care about.

00:31:18.835 --> 00:31:24.424
But if you felt like I was overstepping, I'm sorry.

00:31:41.441 --> 00:31:46.905
INCOMING CALL KIM JIUNG :cue

00:31:59.292 --> 00:32:00.626
Granny.

00:32:00.627 --> 00:32:03.212
Oh, come in. How are things at the staff quarters?

00:32:03.213 --> 00:32:04.673
Is everything to your liking?

00:32:05.257 --> 00:32:07.633
I told you to just come to my house.

00:32:07.634 --> 00:32:10.094
Why did you choose such an awkward living arrangement?

00:32:10.095 --> 00:32:11.637
It's not awkward at all.

00:32:11.638 --> 00:32:12.931
Oh, please.

00:32:13.765 --> 00:32:16.475
If things aren't awkward, why are you here?

00:32:26.570 --> 00:32:30.072
By the way, are you going to stop hanging out with that doctor?

00:32:30.073 --> 00:32:31.074
Eh?

00:32:31.825 --> 00:32:34.202
Don't be so hard on him.

00:32:35.078 --> 00:32:38.415
Mija was actually relieved that he was around.

00:32:39.916 --> 00:32:44.004
I'm sure Mija's relieved that you have a good man by your side.

00:32:51.178 --> 00:32:55.015
Granny, on second thought, I think I'll just head back.

00:32:58.059 --> 00:32:59.394
You turn in for the night.

00:33:02.814 --> 00:33:03.815
Take care.

00:33:08.737 --> 00:33:10.905
Goodness.

00:33:20.624 --> 00:33:21.625
Huh?

00:33:43.104 --> 00:33:44.439
What are you doing here?

00:33:46.399 --> 00:33:49.736
Oh, I just came out for a walk because I was bored.

00:33:50.320 --> 00:33:53.156
But I think this streetlight's broken.

00:33:53.823 --> 00:33:56.243
Should I go to Mr. Park to have it dealt with?

00:34:08.838 --> 00:34:10.924
Have you had dinner yet?

00:34:11.883 --> 00:34:13.134
I haven't.

00:34:29.985 --> 00:34:31.111
Dr. Hyeon.

00:34:33.947 --> 00:34:34.948
Thank you.

00:34:38.243 --> 00:34:39.452
I know all about it.

00:34:40.370 --> 00:34:42.497
How you must have had to go out of your way

00:34:43.164 --> 00:34:45.792
To get my grandma into the clinical trials.

00:34:48.503 --> 00:34:51.506
I've been meaning to thank you.

00:34:52.299 --> 00:34:55.010
For looking into treatments for my grandma,

00:34:55.677 --> 00:34:58.388
And also for putting up with my ridiculous requests.

00:35:01.266 --> 00:35:02.267
And also

00:35:09.065 --> 00:35:10.358
For liking me.

00:35:17.407 --> 00:35:18.742
But you should stop now.

00:35:22.495 --> 00:35:24.664
I know it's really hard on you too.

00:35:25.457 --> 00:35:27.876
:cue

00:35:55.862 --> 00:35:57.530
Is it because of Dr. Do Jiui?

00:36:05.538 --> 00:36:07.540
Has your attempt to blame him for everything

00:36:09.042 --> 00:36:10.043
Failed?

00:36:16.216 --> 00:36:17.217
Mm-hmm.

00:36:25.975 --> 00:36:29.437
You cried all the time when you were with him, though.

00:36:47.080 --> 00:36:48.581
I'll also try

00:36:49.916 --> 00:36:51.418
To stop liking you.

00:36:53.044 --> 00:36:56.131
But you know how hard that is.

00:37:04.848 --> 00:37:05.932
Shall we eat?

00:37:10.311 --> 00:37:11.438
Mmm.

00:37:13.064 --> 00:37:14.441
That's good.

00:37:37.547 --> 00:37:38.590
Does it still hurt?

00:37:39.257 --> 00:37:40.340
Yes.

00:37:40.341 --> 00:37:43.093
What the heck is causing these muscle aches anyway?

00:37:43.094 --> 00:37:46.722
I just had to take care of some stuff.

00:37:46.723 --> 00:37:47.932
Some stuff?

00:37:49.559 --> 00:37:52.019
You need to get your priorities straight!

00:37:52.020 --> 00:37:55.940
Don't you see how Ms. Hari and Dr. Chiyeon's rooms are empty?

00:37:56.649 --> 00:37:59.443
Instead of sticking those pain relief patches on,

00:37:59.444 --> 00:38:01.862
You should be sticking to her if you like her.

00:38:01.863 --> 00:38:03.740
That's what it means to like someone!

00:38:05.074 --> 00:38:07.701
You ninnyhammer.

00:38:07.702 --> 00:38:08.912
MS. HWANG SINHYE

00:38:11.581 --> 00:38:12.706
Hello?

00:38:12.707 --> 00:38:14.541
Dr. Do, you're at the center, right?

00:38:14.542 --> 00:38:17.044
I've just been told that a patient is headed there.

00:38:17.045 --> 00:38:18.379
A patient?

00:38:19.005 --> 00:38:20.632
I got a few bug bites.

00:38:21.341 --> 00:38:24.259
But it's been itching so much

00:38:24.260 --> 00:38:31.226
That I've been having trouble falling asleep.

00:38:32.101 --> 00:38:33.102
Goodness.

00:38:33.978 --> 00:38:36.814
What were mosquitoes even doing out in winter anyway?

00:38:36.815 --> 00:38:39.191
They really got me good.

00:38:39.192 --> 00:38:41.527
But it seems the bites are only on one side.

00:38:41.528 --> 00:38:47.115
I'm a heavy sleeper, you see.

00:38:47.116 --> 00:38:49.034
Any other symptoms?

00:38:49.035 --> 00:38:51.371
Oh, none whatsoever.

00:38:51.955 --> 00:38:55.541
I'll prescribe you some ointment you can apply whenever it itches.

00:38:55.542 --> 00:38:57.001
Okay.

00:39:03.842 --> 00:39:05.134
Be safe on your way back.

00:39:10.557 --> 00:39:12.433
One of his legs

00:39:15.895 --> 00:39:17.980
He has an asymmetrical gait.

00:39:17.981 --> 00:39:19.649
Right?

00:39:22.652 --> 00:39:25.738
How long have you been standing there?

00:39:26.573 --> 00:39:27.574
I just got here.

00:39:28.783 --> 00:39:29.951
What were you doing here?

00:39:33.204 --> 00:39:34.247
Dr. Do.

00:39:35.206 --> 00:39:37.541
- Want to go running together? - What?

00:39:37.542 --> 00:39:40.712
I know you're also having trouble falling asleep anyway. :cue

00:39:56.978 --> 00:39:58.896
Don't push yourself too hard.

00:39:58.897 --> 00:40:00.606
Push myself too hard? Not at all.

00:40:00.607 --> 00:40:04.068
I'm just worried you might overdo it so late at night.

00:40:06.863 --> 00:40:07.864
Guess we'll find out.

00:40:09.115 --> 00:40:10.325
Hey, wait!

00:40:14.120 --> 00:40:15.371
Wait! Damn it.

00:40:17.790 --> 00:40:20.000
Seriously? Cheap move, man!

00:40:20.001 --> 00:40:21.461
- Try to keep up! - What?

00:40:23.755 --> 00:40:24.756
Shit

00:40:26.007 --> 00:40:27.133
Yeah!

00:40:30.678 --> 00:40:31.679
Damn it

00:40:42.523 --> 00:40:44.734
Wait up.

00:40:45.610 --> 00:40:47.778
Wait

00:40:47.779 --> 00:40:49.655
Wait! Wait!

00:40:49.656 --> 00:40:51.782
Wait Wait. Wait.

00:40:58.081 --> 00:41:00.165
Looks like you could use some more exercise.

00:41:00.166 --> 00:41:02.084
It's not like that, okay?

00:41:02.085 --> 00:41:05.796
Overworking yourself before going to bed only gets in the way of sleep

00:41:11.010 --> 00:41:14.305
- Oh, man. - I really don't get it.

00:41:16.683 --> 00:41:18.142
What do you mean?

00:41:20.853 --> 00:41:23.231
I've got more going for me than just my stamina.

00:41:23.940 --> 00:41:26.567
I'm fairly handsome, and I come from a decent family.

00:41:28.194 --> 00:41:30.320
Wouldn't anyone agree that I'm the better option?

00:41:30.321 --> 00:41:31.990
What's with the sudden monologue?

00:41:34.534 --> 00:41:35.535
I'm just annoyed

00:41:37.912 --> 00:41:40.665
That Ms. Hari chose you and not me.

00:41:45.420 --> 00:41:47.547
Be good to Ms. Hari.

00:41:48.423 --> 00:41:51.259
She's always alone, and it breaks my heart.

00:41:55.263 --> 00:41:57.974
What am I even saying?

00:42:04.355 --> 00:42:07.316
- Let's go. - Oh :cue

00:42:57.533 --> 00:43:01.453
Man, why do I have to deal with such nonsense so early in the morning?

00:43:01.454 --> 00:43:02.996
- Higher! - Okay!

00:43:02.997 --> 00:43:04.873
- Raise it a little higher! - Okay.

00:43:04.874 --> 00:43:07.042
Yes. Tie it! That's it! Yep!

00:43:07.043 --> 00:43:08.794
CELEBRATING THE HELIPAD RENEWAL

00:43:08.795 --> 00:43:10.545
PYEONDONGDO WELCOMES GOVERNOR KO

00:43:10.546 --> 00:43:12.672
Have a seat. I'll get you your medicine.

00:43:12.673 --> 00:43:15.468
Sure.

00:43:17.220 --> 00:43:18.221
Huh?

00:43:19.222 --> 00:43:20.972
What's with the suit?

00:43:20.973 --> 00:43:23.975
You helped with the banners and you still don't get it?

00:43:23.976 --> 00:43:26.229
It's an inaugural celebration for the helipad.

00:43:26.813 --> 00:43:30.191
The county office asked me to deliver a speech as the village chief.

00:43:30.942 --> 00:43:32.943
The governor will be attending.

00:43:32.944 --> 00:43:35.612
Why would they care about what a village chief has to say?

00:43:35.613 --> 00:43:37.572
Enough. Just take your meds and go.

00:43:37.573 --> 00:43:39.324
What's there to celebrate

00:43:39.325 --> 00:43:42.494
About tearing down a working helipad and rebuilding it?

00:43:42.495 --> 00:43:44.288
With local elections coming up,

00:43:45.248 --> 00:43:48.083
I'm sure he needed some tangible results to save face.

00:43:48.084 --> 00:43:50.293
If he wanted tangible results,

00:43:50.294 --> 00:43:53.922
He could have gotten us an X-ray machine instead.

00:43:55.091 --> 00:43:58.386
I guess getting X-ray machines for the health center lacks pizzazz.

00:44:00.221 --> 00:44:02.931
Oh, my. I hope you're not all busy right now.

00:44:02.932 --> 00:44:06.726
Goodness, Mr. Park, you're looking sharp today.

00:44:06.727 --> 00:44:07.979
What are you doing here?

00:44:08.563 --> 00:44:10.021
Come out, everyone!

00:44:10.022 --> 00:44:11.566
I've got an announcement to make.

00:44:13.985 --> 00:44:17.112
Damn, what's with those sour looks on your faces?

00:44:17.113 --> 00:44:20.700
You're hurting my feelings, okay?

00:44:21.868 --> 00:44:24.453
- Here's the official notice. - What's it about?

00:44:27.874 --> 00:44:30.000
It's an official notice requesting

00:44:30.001 --> 00:44:35.088
All of our esteemed PH docs to attend the helipad inauguration ceremony today.

00:44:35.089 --> 00:44:38.800
Why do you need doctors and nurses to attend a helipad inauguration?

00:44:38.801 --> 00:44:41.469
What if an urgent patient shows up?

00:44:41.470 --> 00:44:44.931
At worst, they'll be dealing with the common cold or athlete's foot,

00:44:44.932 --> 00:44:46.558
So tell them to just suck it up.

00:44:46.559 --> 00:44:48.727
The governor's traveling a long way, so you should be there.

00:44:48.728 --> 00:44:52.939
Who does the governor think he is, the president?

00:44:52.940 --> 00:44:56.776
Ma'am! The governor is indeed the president in Yeopoong-gun!

00:44:56.777 --> 00:44:59.237
And I'm the prime minister, his second-in-command!

00:44:59.238 --> 00:45:02.949
This right here is an official notice!

00:45:02.950 --> 00:45:07.662
And as civil servants, you have to comply.

00:45:07.663 --> 00:45:10.916
With next year's budget execution right around the corner,

00:45:10.917 --> 00:45:16.129
A win for Yeopoong-gun will be a win for all of you.

00:45:16.130 --> 00:45:17.839
Wouldn't you agree?

00:45:19.175 --> 00:45:21.301
I'd better see you all later. Okay?

00:45:28.100 --> 00:45:29.185
Wachow!

00:45:29.852 --> 00:45:30.853
Bam!

00:45:31.479 --> 00:45:33.314
Who the hell does he think he is?

00:45:34.941 --> 00:45:36.359
Punk-ass brat

00:45:39.946 --> 00:45:43.990
What did they call the chopper for when there's no patient?

00:45:43.991 --> 00:45:47.036
They always complain to us about how much calling one costs.

00:45:48.079 --> 00:45:49.330
It's all for show.

00:45:49.830 --> 00:45:51.332
There's your answer.

00:45:51.916 --> 00:45:54.000
The governor's very own dog-and-pony show.

00:45:56.754 --> 00:45:59.464
But what's taking the governor so long?

00:45:59.465 --> 00:46:01.716
We must have waited an hour for him already.

00:46:01.717 --> 00:46:04.803
What kind of VIP would he be if he arrived early for such a venue?

00:46:04.804 --> 00:46:08.223
The star of the show's always supposed to make a point of arriving late.

00:46:08.224 --> 00:46:09.849
-  Goodness - When the governor arrives,

00:46:09.850 --> 00:46:11.268
Pin a flower on him.

00:46:11.269 --> 00:46:12.561
He's here!

00:46:18.025 --> 00:46:21.194
My, my, what lovely weather we have!

00:46:21.195 --> 00:46:22.404
Goodness, thank you.

00:46:22.405 --> 00:46:24.364
That's good.

00:46:24.365 --> 00:46:26.199
My, if it isn't Dr. Do Jiui.

00:46:26.200 --> 00:46:29.161
So how are things now that you've returned to your patients?

00:46:30.079 --> 00:46:31.997
Ah, I've been getting by.

00:46:31.998 --> 00:46:34.749
Funny how there are always cameras around when I see you, Governor.

00:46:34.750 --> 00:46:39.796
My, I see you've been working on your jokes, Dr. Do.

00:46:39.797 --> 00:46:42.132
Hello.

00:46:42.133 --> 00:46:44.175
- Oh, my. Hello. - Get up. :cue

00:46:44.176 --> 00:46:46.470
- Oh, my. - I'm the village chief.

00:46:47.513 --> 00:46:49.431
I'm Lee Jangsu.

00:46:49.432 --> 00:46:50.515
Now!

00:46:50.516 --> 00:46:52.976
Okay, everyone. Please take your seats!

00:46:52.977 --> 00:46:54.561
Hello.

00:46:54.562 --> 00:46:59.566
Firstly, let's hear a word from Governor Ko Changmok,

00:46:59.567 --> 00:47:04.738
Who spared no effort in aiding the construction of the helipad!

00:47:04.739 --> 00:47:06.906
Let's give him a big round of applause!

00:47:08.200 --> 00:47:13.747
Ko Changmok! Ko Changmok! Ko Changmok!

00:47:13.748 --> 00:47:18.085
My heart is bursting with joy!

00:47:19.170 --> 00:47:21.296
We were only able to wrap up

00:47:21.297 --> 00:47:25.091
The construction of this helipad so quickly,

00:47:25.092 --> 00:47:31.307
Thanks to the unwavering support of Pyeondongdo's residents.

00:47:32.308 --> 00:47:33.975
- This is a day of celebration - Sir

00:47:33.976 --> 00:47:35.727
- Yes? - Hello.

00:47:35.728 --> 00:47:40.483
Did someone named Lee Hongsik visit the health center, by any chance?

00:47:42.902 --> 00:47:44.695
- Mr. Lee Hongsik? - Yes.

00:47:45.571 --> 00:47:46.655
All this time, Pyeon

00:47:48.240 --> 00:47:51.826
Pyeondongdo, given its geographic conditions

00:47:51.827 --> 00:47:58.541
When I got back from the mainland, my husband was missing

00:47:58.542 --> 00:48:00.210
And he didn't answer his phone.

00:48:00.211 --> 00:48:03.838
Last night, he told me he was going to revisit the health center

00:48:03.839 --> 00:48:06.634
Because his ointment wasn't doing anything for him.

00:48:08.177 --> 00:48:11.262
What were mosquitoes even doing out in winter anyway?

00:48:11.263 --> 00:48:13.431
They really got me good.

00:48:13.432 --> 00:48:15.975
Any other symptoms?

00:48:15.976 --> 00:48:18.062
Oh, none whatsoever.

00:48:20.106 --> 00:48:21.481
Aside from skin issues,

00:48:21.482 --> 00:48:24.526
Does Mr. Lee Hongsik suffer from any other conditions?

00:48:24.527 --> 00:48:25.653
Like Parkinson's?

00:48:26.654 --> 00:48:28.321
Goodness, how did you

00:48:28.322 --> 00:48:29.531
Oh, my

00:48:29.532 --> 00:48:35.370
My husband told me to keep his Parkinson's a secret, no matter what.

00:48:35.371 --> 00:48:38.373
- You haven't heard back since last night? - Yes.

00:48:38.374 --> 00:48:40.125
Mr. Lee only had bites on one side,

00:48:40.126 --> 00:48:43.795
So he must have suffered from nighttime rigidity for some time.

00:48:43.796 --> 00:48:45.672
He could be in danger. We have to find him.

00:48:45.673 --> 00:48:47.173
- Nighttime rigidity? - Ms. Hwang.

00:48:47.174 --> 00:48:49.592
Yes. Oh, my What do we do?

00:48:49.593 --> 00:48:51.344
Oh, my

00:48:51.345 --> 00:48:53.513
What do we do?

00:48:53.514 --> 00:48:55.390
- Mr. Park. - Right now, we

00:48:55.391 --> 00:48:57.308
One of the villagers has gone missing.

00:48:57.309 --> 00:48:58.726
They've gone missing?

00:48:58.727 --> 00:49:00.270
He apparently has Parkinson's.

00:49:00.271 --> 00:49:02.313
- You need to make an announcement. -  Hey!

00:49:02.314 --> 00:49:03.606
- We need to -  Hey!

00:49:03.607 --> 00:49:06.276
What are you doing right now? Sit down!

00:49:06.277 --> 00:49:08.027
We need to all look for him.

00:49:08.028 --> 00:49:10.029
What's his name?

00:49:10.030 --> 00:49:11.281
Mr. Lee Hongsik.

00:49:11.282 --> 00:49:14.451
- providing a patient with immediate care - I said, sit down!

00:49:14.452 --> 00:49:17.120
Governor, something urgent has come up.

00:49:17.121 --> 00:49:19.456
- So if you would lend me the mic - Mr. Park!

00:49:19.457 --> 00:49:21.958
Can't you see the governor's in the middle of his speech?

00:49:21.959 --> 00:49:24.377
- I told you, I have something to say! - Let go of him.

00:49:24.378 --> 00:49:26.421
You heard the man. He has something to say.

00:49:26.422 --> 00:49:27.505
Hurry

00:49:27.506 --> 00:49:29.632
Distance will no longer be a limiting factor

00:49:29.633 --> 00:49:32.635
In providing a patient with immediate care

00:49:32.636 --> 00:49:37.599
I have an announcement for all Pyeondong residents present.

00:49:37.600 --> 00:49:41.644
So Mr. Lee Hongsik, who has Parkinson's disease,

00:49:41.645 --> 00:49:43.980
Has gone missing.

00:49:43.981 --> 00:49:47.066
We'd like your help looking for Mr. Lee Hongsik.

00:49:47.067 --> 00:49:49.486
- We'd appreciate your cooperation! -  This is urgent!

00:49:49.487 --> 00:49:51.863
-  Mr. Lee Hongsik! -  What?

00:49:51.864 --> 00:49:52.947
Where are you going?

00:49:52.948 --> 00:49:54.824
The governor's in the middle of his speech!

00:49:54.825 --> 00:49:57.660
Who cares about the governor when a man's life is in peril?

00:49:57.661 --> 00:49:59.329
Byeongcheol!

00:49:59.330 --> 00:50:02.833
Grow a conscience for once, and do the right thing!

00:50:03.459 --> 00:50:06.211
Why, you!

00:50:06.212 --> 00:50:08.087
- Sit back down! - But

00:50:08.088 --> 00:50:10.298
We'll be giving you a gift after this is over!

00:50:10.299 --> 00:50:11.884
Mr. Lee Hongsik!

00:50:12.468 --> 00:50:14.094
Mr. Lee!

00:50:14.637 --> 00:50:16.679
He can't have made it this far, though.

00:50:16.680 --> 00:50:18.973
You're right. Maybe we should try this way

00:50:18.974 --> 00:50:20.099
- I'll go this way. - Okay.

00:50:20.100 --> 00:50:22.061
- Why don't we go this way? - Go that way.

00:50:23.687 --> 00:50:24.979
Sir!

00:50:24.980 --> 00:50:26.606
Mr. Lee!

00:50:26.607 --> 00:50:27.816
Mr. Lee Hongsik!

00:50:28.984 --> 00:50:30.110
Sir!

00:50:31.737 --> 00:50:33.072
Mr. Lee! :cue

00:50:36.325 --> 00:50:38.243
- Mr. Lee! - Honey!

00:50:38.244 --> 00:50:40.036
Mr. Lee!

00:50:40.037 --> 00:50:42.665
Honey!

00:50:43.332 --> 00:50:44.375
Oh, gosh

00:50:45.918 --> 00:50:47.294
Mr. Lee!

00:50:48.254 --> 00:50:49.630
This is bad.

00:50:54.134 --> 00:50:55.177
What is it?

00:51:01.934 --> 00:51:02.935
Mr. Lee!

00:51:03.769 --> 00:51:05.436
Wait just a moment. We'll come down!

00:51:05.437 --> 00:51:07.648
No, stay here. I'll go.

00:51:10.025 --> 00:51:11.235
Be careful.

00:51:17.157 --> 00:51:18.241
Are you okay?

00:51:18.242 --> 00:51:19.867
Mr. Lee.

00:51:19.868 --> 00:51:22.537
Are you okay?

00:51:22.538 --> 00:51:24.290
Don't worry. I'm a doctor.

00:51:25.124 --> 00:51:26.667
I'm sorry.

00:51:28.085 --> 00:51:34.048
My legs stopped working all of a sudden, and

00:51:34.049 --> 00:51:35.467
It's okay, sir.

00:51:36.051 --> 00:51:38.804
Dr. Do, I'll let them know that we found the patient.

00:51:39.305 --> 00:51:40.306
Wait

00:51:41.515 --> 00:51:42.725
Hold on.

00:51:44.476 --> 00:51:49.690
I don't want anyone else to know about this.

00:52:00.159 --> 00:52:03.745
Ms. Yuk, he doesn't seem to have any severe injuries,

00:52:03.746 --> 00:52:05.371
So I'll help him get back up there.

00:52:05.372 --> 00:52:06.748
Okay.

00:52:06.749 --> 00:52:09.208
- Sir, can you get up? - Yes.

00:52:09.209 --> 00:52:11.419
Let's try getting you up. One, two

00:52:13.631 --> 00:52:15.965
It's a relief we found you.

00:52:15.966 --> 00:52:18.176
Your wife was worried sick, sir.

00:52:18.177 --> 00:52:21.638
Gosh, I've caused so much trouble for everyone

00:52:21.639 --> 00:52:25.683
-  Oh, goodness, honey! - Careful, ma'am.

00:52:25.684 --> 00:52:27.686
Honey!

00:52:29.396 --> 00:52:31.939
Are you injured? Does it hurt anywhere?

00:52:31.940 --> 00:52:36.402
We could have pretended nothing happened if you had just let it pass.

00:52:36.403 --> 00:52:41.450
Why'd you have to get everyone involved and make such a big deal out of nothing?

00:52:42.451 --> 00:52:46.204
This is so humiliating!

00:52:46.205 --> 00:52:48.665
I was just so worried about you.

00:52:48.666 --> 00:52:52.752
You just had to make such a big deal out of nothing!

00:52:54.338 --> 00:52:56.506
Goodness, thank you.

00:52:56.507 --> 00:52:58.384
Thank you so much.

00:52:59.968 --> 00:53:02.011
He must be in shock.

00:53:02.012 --> 00:53:05.432
Yes. Goodness, I'm okay.

00:53:06.016 --> 00:53:11.604
He wasn't lashing out because he was mad at me.

00:53:11.605 --> 00:53:15.316
It's because he's mad at himself.

00:53:15.317 --> 00:53:18.820
He wants to get better, but it's not working out.

00:53:18.821 --> 00:53:25.243
So he's having a hard time admitting that he's sick.

00:53:25.244 --> 00:53:26.578
Oh, goodness

00:53:35.421 --> 00:53:37.797
Are you kidding me right now?

00:53:37.798 --> 00:53:41.759
You couldn't stop one man and made me look like a clown up there!

00:53:41.760 --> 00:53:43.637
I tried to stop him, but

00:53:44.388 --> 00:53:46.889
I'll round up the reporters one more time, sir.

00:53:46.890 --> 00:53:48.975
Next time, we'll even invite a bunch of A-list celebrities and--

00:53:51.603 --> 00:53:53.521
Why should I entrust you with anything

00:53:53.522 --> 00:53:56.232
When you can't even manage a puny island properly? Huh?

00:53:56.233 --> 00:53:57.316
Apologies, sir.

00:53:57.317 --> 00:53:59.610
- If you would give me one more chance-- - A chance?

00:53:59.611 --> 00:54:01.028
Not in your wildest dreams.

00:54:01.029 --> 00:54:03.406
I'd better not ever see you around again.

00:54:03.407 --> 00:54:04.490
I mean it.

00:54:04.491 --> 00:54:06.242
- I mean it! - We should get going, sir.

00:54:06.243 --> 00:54:08.620
Sir, wait. Please!

00:54:09.288 --> 00:54:13.041
If you were to give me one last chance, I, Yeom Byeongcheol

00:54:13.667 --> 00:54:16.170
I, Yeom Byeongcheol, will lay down my life :cue

00:54:18.172 --> 00:54:20.506
Oh, my. Hello.

00:54:21.717 --> 00:54:24.344
I'm going to buy some sweet ice cream.

00:54:25.971 --> 00:54:26.972
Hmm.

00:54:35.481 --> 00:54:38.983
I'm sorry, but that one's my girlfriend's favorite.

00:54:46.158 --> 00:54:49.827
Well, maybe she won't mind the chocolate-flavored one.

00:54:49.828 --> 00:54:53.916
Damn, I just snagged the last one.

00:54:55.542 --> 00:54:56.543
Yeah.

00:54:57.586 --> 00:54:59.171
Do you need anything else?

00:55:01.423 --> 00:55:02.507
How much is this?

00:55:02.508 --> 00:55:04.091
- That'll be 4,000 won. - 4,000 won?

00:55:04.092 --> 00:55:06.178
- I'd also like a bag, please. - Okay.

00:55:07.888 --> 00:55:08.889
Sure.

00:55:17.272 --> 00:55:18.565
Hmm.

00:55:43.549 --> 00:55:48.094
Ms. Eom, I got you ice cream

00:55:48.095 --> 00:55:49.096
Huh?

00:55:51.723 --> 00:55:52.724
Huh?

00:56:11.034 --> 00:56:12.494
So Ms. Eom's friend

00:56:17.332 --> 00:56:18.625
Is a guy?

00:56:20.377 --> 00:56:21.711
PH DOC DO'S SWIFT JUDGMENT

00:56:21.712 --> 00:56:23.422
Oh, for the love of

00:56:27.426 --> 00:56:29.928
What the hell is all this?

00:56:30.846 --> 00:56:35.266
You couldn't even stop an article like this from getting out?

00:56:35.267 --> 00:56:37.603
How could you be so incompetent?

00:56:38.353 --> 00:56:41.106
And what the hell is this punk's problem? Huh?

00:56:42.524 --> 00:56:44.860
The article's littered with slander against me!

00:56:45.402 --> 00:56:49.698
Damn it, being a governor's such a thankless job!

00:56:50.657 --> 00:56:55.286
Goodness me. That photo sure came out great, huh?

00:56:55.287 --> 00:56:56.871
What did I tell you?

00:56:56.872 --> 00:56:59.123
I told you that suit wasn't just for show,

00:56:59.124 --> 00:57:01.792
And I told you I'd get a word in!

00:57:01.793 --> 00:57:04.337
You made it into the shot too, way in the back.

00:57:04.338 --> 00:57:05.339
Did you see it?

00:57:06.965 --> 00:57:10.677
I guess he doesn't like how he looks.

00:57:11.219 --> 00:57:13.721
- That's right. Ms. Hari. - Yes?

00:57:13.722 --> 00:57:15.932
- Can I pull you aside for a second? - Mm-hmm.

00:57:22.272 --> 00:57:25.608
You all look like a bunch of Seoulites. You all look great.

00:57:25.609 --> 00:57:27.069
- Please take a seat. - Okay.

00:57:31.073 --> 00:57:33.032
Living without a home is taking a toll, isn't it?

00:57:33.033 --> 00:57:34.950
Not at all.

00:57:34.951 --> 00:57:37.036
Taking a look at your house,

00:57:37.037 --> 00:57:39.331
We've found a lot of things that need fixing.

00:57:40.499 --> 00:57:44.960
Giving the house a full makeover while we're at it would be nice.

00:57:44.961 --> 00:57:47.297
But truth be told,

00:57:48.340 --> 00:57:51.593
I'm hesitant because I'm not sure how long you'll be on the island. :cue

00:57:53.428 --> 00:57:54.513
Ah

00:57:55.931 --> 00:57:58.350
Since you're not from here, and

00:58:00.811 --> 00:58:03.271
Granny Mija's no longer with us.

00:58:05.565 --> 00:58:07.149
If you'll be leaving someday,

00:58:07.150 --> 00:58:09.778
I don't know if you'd want to use that much money.

00:58:10.362 --> 00:58:14.198
Do think it over and let me know.

00:58:14.199 --> 00:58:16.243
- Mm-hmm. - I'll be going now. Okay?

00:59:58.678 --> 01:00:00.055
Huh?

01:00:22.536 --> 01:00:23.703
Dr. Do.

01:00:29.668 --> 01:00:30.794
Ms. Yuk.

01:00:45.892 --> 01:00:47.394
What is the matter with you?

01:00:51.648 --> 01:00:53.692
I'm sorry for doing this without your permission.

01:01:00.073 --> 01:01:01.783
All I've done is treat you horribly.

01:01:04.911 --> 01:01:06.412
All I've done is mistreat you,

01:01:06.413 --> 01:01:08.915
But why do you keep playing the nice guy with me?

01:01:17.591 --> 01:01:18.925
I'm not a nice person.

01:01:22.262 --> 01:01:25.265
That's why I can't do as you ask and go on pretending I don't see you. :cue

01:01:30.061 --> 01:01:31.062
I can't do it.

01:01:32.105 --> 01:01:33.565
I can't ignore you.

01:01:38.403 --> 01:01:42.449
I can't help it, even if it makes you hate me, so

01:01:46.995 --> 01:01:48.997
Can't you just put up with me?

01:03:42.110 --> 01:03:45.070
I DON'T HATE YOU OR ANYTHING

01:03:45.071 --> 01:03:51.619
BUT EVERY TIME I SEE YOU, I FEEL LIKE BREAKING DOWN IN TEARS.

01:04:04.799 --> 01:04:08.219
ALWAYS WONDERED HOW THINGS LOOKED FROM BEHIND THE CAMERA

01:04:08.803 --> 01:04:11.305
GRANDMA'S PHOTO IS BASICALLY A CHEAT CODE

01:04:11.306 --> 01:04:13.349
JUST LOOKING AT IT MAKES ME TEAR UP

01:04:20.315 --> 01:04:23.234
DOCTOR ON THE EDGE

01:04:24.611 --> 01:04:27.404
Isn't it an emergency if contaminated IV fluid was administered?

01:04:27.405 --> 01:04:28.864
Hurry!

01:04:28.865 --> 01:04:30.992
This is clearly an illegal medical practice.

01:04:32.577 --> 01:04:34.787
We're going to need you to head over there.

01:04:34.788 --> 01:04:35.913
I'll go with him.

01:04:35.914 --> 01:04:37.164
Mmm!

01:04:37.165 --> 01:04:40.752
Ferry service has been suspended today due to the strong winds.

01:04:41.461 --> 01:04:43.253
I guess only one room was available.

01:04:43.254 --> 01:04:46.257
You're a nice boy who doesn't like crossing the line, aren't you?

01:04:48.301 --> 01:04:49.928
No, I'm not.

01:04:52.806 --> 01:04:54.808
Translated by Yoon Hyuk Park

